    intro: "Concert outfits should make you feel like yourself — just turned up to 10. Whether you're at an intimate jazz venue, an outdoor festival, or an arena show, the right look balances self-expression with practicality: comfortable footwear, weather-ready layers, and pieces that move with you.",
    faq: [
      { q: "What should I wear to a concert?", a: "Match the artist's vibe and the venue. For outdoor festivals, layer up with a denim jacket and comfortable boots. For arena shows, anything goes — this is your moment to express yourself. For classical concerts, smart-casual or semi-formal is appropriate." },
      { q: "What shoes should I wear to a concert?", a: "Comfort is key at concerts. You'll likely be standing for hours. Ankle boots, chunky trainers, or comfortable flat shoes work best. Save heels for seated venues." },
    ],
  },
  "birthday-party-outfits": {
    slug: "birthday-party-outfits", occasion: "birthday-party",
    h1: "Birthday Party Outfit Ideas",
    title: "Birthday Party Outfit Ideas — What to Wear to a Birthday",
    metaDesc: "Dress to impress at any birthday party. Style guides for men and women — from casual backyard gatherings to upscale celebrations.",
    intro: "Birthday parties come in every shape and size — from low-key backyard barbecues to upscale rooftop dinners. The right outfit depends on the venue, time of day, and how well you know the host. These guides break it down by season and style so you always show up looking the part.",
    faq: [
      { q: "What should I wear to a birthday party?", a: "For a casual birthday gathering, smart-casual works well — dark jeans, a nice top, and clean shoes. For an upscale birthday dinner or club night, elevate with a blazer, dress, or statement piece. When in doubt, dress one level above what you'd normally wear to the venue." },
      { q: "Is there a dress code for birthday parties?", a: "Most birthday party invitations don't specify a dress code unless it's a formal event. Read the venue and time of day as your guide: house party = casual; restaurant dinner = smart-casual; rooftop or nightclub = dressed up." },
    ],
  },
  "business-meeting-outfits": {
    slug: "business-meeting-outfits", occasion: "business-meeting",
    h1: "Business Meeting Outfit Ideas",
    title: "Business Meeting Outfits — Professional Style Guides for Men & Women",
    metaDesc: "Dress with authority at your next business meeting. Professional outfit guides for men and women — corporate, smart-casual, and creative industries.",
    intro: "What you wear to a business meeting communicates your professionalism before you've said a word. The right business outfit varies by industry and meeting type — a board presentation calls for something different than a client lunch or a networking event. These guides cover every scenario across all seasons.",
    faq: [
      { q: "What should I wear to a business meeting?", a: "For formal business meetings, a well-fitted suit in navy, grey, or charcoal is the gold standard. For smart-casual business settings, tailored trousers, a quality shirt, and leather shoes convey professionalism. Always prioritise fit over labels." },
      { q: "Can I wear smart-casual to a business meeting?", a: "In many industries, smart-casual is perfectly appropriate — especially for internal meetings, creative sectors, or tech companies. Well-fitted chinos, a blazer, and leather shoes or polished trainers read professional without being overly formal." },
    ],
