    h1: "Casual Outing Outfit Ideas",
    title: "Casual Outing Outfit Ideas for Men & Women",
    metaDesc: "Look great without overthinking it. Effortless casual outfit ideas for men and women — shopping trips, coffee dates, weekend errands, and more.",
    intro: "Casual outings are where personal style shines most. Without a strict dress code, the best casual outfits feel effortless, comfortable, and genuinely you. Whether you're running errands, grabbing coffee with friends, or heading to a weekend market, these guides give you real options for every season.",
    faq: [
      { q: "What makes a good casual outfit?", a: "A good casual outfit looks intentional without feeling forced. Well-fitted basics — clean jeans or chinos, a quality tee or shirt, and understated trainers or loafers — form a reliable foundation. Add one interesting piece (a jacket, a bag, an accessory) to make it feel considered." },
      { q: "How casual is too casual?", a: "Avoid anything with stains, tears (unless intentional and styled), visible logos on cheap tees, or mismatched sportswear. Casual means relaxed, not sloppy. Neat, well-fitted clothes in any style qualify as presentable casual." },
    ],
  },
  "dinner-party-outfits": {
    slug: "dinner-party-outfits", occasion: "dinner-party",
    h1: "Dinner Party Outfit Ideas",
    title: "Dinner Party Outfits — What to Wear to a Dinner Party",
    metaDesc: "Dress perfectly for any dinner party. Smart, elegant, and semi-formal outfit guides for men and women — for every season and setting.",
    intro: "Dinner parties are the sweet spot between formal and relaxed — which makes choosing the right outfit genuinely tricky. Too casual and you seem indifferent; too formal and you seem stiff. These guides hit the perfect note for every type of dinner party, from a seated home dinner to a private restaurant booking.",
    faq: [
      { q: "What is the ideal outfit for a dinner party?", a: "Smart-casual to semi-formal is the classic dinner party register. For women, a midi dress, tailored trousers with a silk blouse, or an elegant jumpsuit all work beautifully. For men, chinos or tailored trousers with a blazer and leather shoes is the reliable choice." },
      { q: "Is a dinner party the same dress code as cocktail attire?", a: "Not always. Cocktail attire is more formal — typically a suit or cocktail dress. Dinner party dress code is usually smart-casual or semi-formal, unless the invitation specifies otherwise. Read the venue and host's style as your guide." },
    ],
  },
  "eid-celebration-outfits": {
    slug: "eid-celebration-outfits", occasion: "eid-celebration",
    h1: "Eid Celebration Outfit Ideas",
    title: "Eid Outfit Ideas — What to Wear for Eid al-Fitr & Eid al-Adha",
    metaDesc: "Dress beautifully for Eid. Traditional and modern outfit guides for men and women — modest, elegant, and festive looks for every style.",
    intro: "Eid is one of the most joyful and photographed occasions of the year. The right Eid outfit balances tradition, elegance, and personal style — whether you prefer a classic thobe or kandura, a modern abaya, or a fusion of cultural and contemporary fashion. These guides help you find a look that honours the occasion and feels authentically you.",
    faq: [
      { q: "What do people typically wear for Eid?", a: "For Eid prayer and celebrations, men traditionally wear a thobe, kandura, or a smart suit. Women often wear an elegant abaya, jalabiya, or a formal dress. Both traditional and modern modest fashion are widely celebrated — the key is looking polished and festive." },
      { q: "Can I wear Western clothing for Eid?", a: "Absolutely. Many people choose smart Western attire for Eid — a sharp suit for men, or an elegant midi dress or formal trousers for women. The priority is looking polished and respectful of the occasion, regardless of cultural origin." },
    ],
  },
  "engagement-party-outfits": {
    slug: "engagement-party-outfits", occasion: "engagement-party",
    h1: "Engagement Party Outfit Ideas",
    title: "Engagement Party Outfits — What to Wear as a Guest",
    metaDesc: "Celebrate in style. Outfit ideas for engagement party guests — men and women, every season, semi-formal to smart-casual.",
    intro: "An engagement party calls for something between a wedding guest outfit and a smart dinner look — festive, polished, and celebratory without upstaging the couple. These guides walk you through the perfect engagement party guest outfits for every season and style preference.",
    faq: [
      { q: "What should a guest wear to an engagement party?", a: "Semi-formal to smart-casual is the standard for engagement parties. For women, a floral or pastel midi dress, a tailored jumpsuit, or elegant trousers with a blouse all work well. For men, chinos or tailored trousers with a blazer and loafers hits the right note." },
      { q: "Can I wear black to an engagement party?", a: "Yes — a well-styled black outfit is entirely appropriate for an engagement party. Opt for elegant cuts, quality fabrics, and add interest through accessories or texture rather than avoiding the colour entirely." },
    ],
  },
  "travel-day-outfits": {
    slug: "travel-day-outfits", occasion: "travel-day",
    h1: "Travel Day Outfit Ideas",
    title: "Travel Day Outfits — What to Wear on a Travel Day",
    metaDesc: "Look great and stay comfortable on any journey. Travel day outfit guides for men and women — flights, road trips, and long-distance trains.",
    intro: "A good travel day outfit is a rare thing: it needs to be comfortable through hours of sitting, flexible enough for changing temperatures, polished enough for arriving at your destination, and practical for security lines and overhead bins. These guides nail that balance for every season and travel type.",
    faq: [
      { q: "What is the best outfit for a travel day?", a: "The best travel outfit balances comfort and presentability. For long flights, smart joggers or comfortable chinos, a breathable layer, and slip-on shoes streamline security. Avoid denim — it's uncomfortable on long journeys. A light jacket is essential for varying cabin temperatures." },
      { q: "Should I dress nicely when travelling by plane?", a: "Looking presentable on a flight has real perks — better treatment from airline staff, higher chance of upgrades, and you'll feel more confident arriving at your destination. Smart-casual is the sweet spot: comfortable but not sloppy." },
    ],
  },
